==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: cocus wood
<hw>co"cus wood`</hw></mhw> <pr>(?)</pr>.
<def>A West Indian wood obtained from the <prodby>granadilla
tree</prodby>, used for making flutes, clarinets, and other musical
instruments.</def> <altsp>[Also spelled
<asp>cocoswood</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> granadilla wood.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> + <source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>c.o.d.</ent>⟦br⟧
